& [DependencyQuestion] is the active audit need
  + [needed_estimate] is an explicit uniform bound on the lattice-spacing derivative of smeared Schwinger functions
  + [needed_operator_control] is a definition and norm bound for the plaquette-derived insertion produced by d_da
  + [needed_sum_control] is proof that summing derivative insertions over lattice plaquettes remains bounded after smearing and renormalization as a goes to zero
  + [needed_uniformity] is constants independent of lattice spacing, volume, and the relevant tempered-distribution seminorms

& [AppendixAReadout] is dependency_check
  + [section_scope] is polymer counting, single-plaquette weight, and Kotecky-Preiss convergence criterion
  + [useful_content] is absolute convergence and volume-independent control for polymer expansion in the stated large-coupling regime
  + [missing_for_appendix_c] is no d_da derivative operator, no Schwinger-function seminorm estimate, no plaquette-sum cancellation or renormalized scaling argument
  + [dependency_match] is no

& [AppendixGReadout] is dependency_check
  + [section_scope] is hierarchical RG induction, scale-cluster expansion, one-loop shift isolation, remainder estimate, and uniform summability
  + [useful_content] is a claimed scale-by-scale summability framework for effective actions
  + [missing_for_appendix_c] is no explicit map from RG remainder bounds to the C.1 Lipschitz constant, no derivative insertion estimate, and no proof that the continuum a-variation is uniformly controlled in Schwinger-function topology
